There are places where full name is rendered:
{noformat}
Patrick Ledbetter &apos;06
{noformat}
when it should be:
{noformat}
Patrick Ledbetter '06
{noformat}

I noticed it next to "Welcome" and following "added by" and "edited by", but may exsist in other places.

It appears to work correctly in Firefox.

Clicking Save after editing a page (in rich text OR wiki editing mode), causes an error dialog to appear stating Error, Line 5651, Object Error.

Debugging into the code shows that the getElementById('capchaResponse') call in the following method is returning null.

// Method checks whether the captchaResponse textfield is empty.
function checkCaptchaResponse()
{
    var captchaTextField = document.getElementById('captchaResponse');

    if (captchaTextField.value == '')
    {
        document.getElementById("captchaError").style.display = "block";
        document.getElementById("captchaResponse").focus();
        return false;
    }
    else
    {
        return true;
    }
}

The page save succeeds after the error dialog is closed.

